  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "y78fv09vmel",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Void generation\n",
    "\n",
    "aleathor can automatically find empty space in a geometry using an octree-based algorithm. This is useful when you have cells that don't fill the entire bounding region — the algorithm identifies void boxes that cover the gaps.\n",
    "\n",
    "The workflow is:\n",
    "1. Build a geometry (cells + outer boundary)\n",
    "2. Run `model.void.generate()` to find empty regions\n",
    "3. Optionally `merge()` the result to reduce the number of void boxes\n",
    "4. Inspect or visualize the void boxes\n",
    "5. Commit them with `model.void.add(voids)` if you want to close the geometry"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "gdak1qa7tkn",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Cells before void generation: 2\n",
      "Void boxes found: 512\n",
      "Void boxes after merge: 1\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Build a simple geometry: a sphere inside a box, with gaps between them\n",
    "model = ath.Model(\"Void generation demo\")\n",
    "\n",
    "model.add_material(1, name=\"Uranium\", density=10.0).add_element(92, 1.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "sphere = ath.Sphere(0, 0, 0, radius=3)\n",
    "outer = ath.RPP(-10, 10, -10, 10, -10, 10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Only add the sphere — the space between sphere and box is undefined\n",
    "model.add_cell(region=-sphere, material=1, density=10.0, name=\"sphere\")\n",
    "# Graveyard (outside world)\n",
    "model.add_cell(region=+outer, material=0, density=0, name=\"graveyard\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Cells before void generation: {len(model.cells)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate void regions within the existing outer boundary.\n",
    "# Passing the region lets consolidation reuse the original RPP surface.\n",
    "voids = model.void.generate(region=-outer, max_depth=3, min_size=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Void boxes found: {len(voids)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Merge to reduce the number of boxes\n",
    "voids.merge()\n",
    "print(f\"Void boxes after merge: {len(voids)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "jf3o5spiic",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "First 5 void boxes (xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax, zmin, zmax):\n",
      "  Box 0: [-10.0,10.0] x [-10.0,10.0] x [-10.0,10.0]  vol=8000.0\n",
      "\n",
      "Total void volume (sum of boxes): 8000.0 cm³\n",
      "Expected void volume (box - sphere): 7886.9 cm³\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Inspect individual void boxes\n",
    "boxes = voids.get_boxes()\n",
    "print(\"First 5 void boxes (xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax, zmin, zmax):\")\n",
    "for i, box in enumerate(boxes[:5]):\n",
    "    xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax, zmin, zmax = box\n",
    "    vol = (xmax - xmin) * (ymax - ymin) * (zmax - zmin)\n",
    "    print(f\"  Box {i}: [{xmin:.1f},{xmax:.1f}] x [{ymin:.1f},{ymax:.1f}] x [{zmin:.1f},{zmax:.1f}]  vol={vol:.1f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Total void volume\n",
    "import math\n",
    "sphere_vol = 4/3 * math.pi * 3**3\n",
    "box_vol = 20**3\n",
    "expected_void = box_vol - sphere_vol\n",
    "print(f\"\\nTotal void volume (sum of boxes): {voids.total_volume():.1f} cm³\")\n",
    "print(f\"Expected void volume (box - sphere): {expected_void:.1f} cm³\")"
   ]
  },
